        <div id="meat" class="meat containsContent containsNavigation containsConNav">
            <main id="content" class="content" role="main">
                <h2 style="margin-top: 0">We're Sorry...</h2>
                <h3>The link you clicked or the URL you typed in didn't work for
                    some reason.</h3>
                <p>This is best known as a <strong>404</strong> error. Here are some of the reasons why
                    that might have happened:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>We might have a bad link on one of our pages, which sent you to the wrong
                        place when you clicked it.
                    </li>
                    <li>You might have typed in the web address incorrectly.</li>
                    <li>Someone might have sent you a message that had an incorrect web address.</li>
                    <li>Our server could be having problems.</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>What were you looking for?</h3>
                <form action="https://www.carleton.edu/search/" method="get" class="form">
                    <p>
                        <label for="combinedSearchInputBody" class="form__label">Search people and pages:</label>
                        <input type="text" id="combinedSearchInputBody" name="q" size="18" class="form__input">
                        <input type="submit" id="combinedSearchSubmitBody" value="Search" class="button--solid form__button">
                    </p>
                </form>
                <p>If you think that there's a bad link on a page, please go back to the page that
                    had the link, and there should be contact information for the person who maintains
                    it at the bottom of the page. Please contact them (email is always
                    good) and let them know about the problem!</p>
                <p>If you can't figure out whom to contact, you can send an email to <a href="mailto:web@carleton.edu">web@carleton.edu</a>.
                    Make sure to let us know where the bad link was located. Thanks!</p>
                <p class="maintained">Maintained by <a href="https://go.carleton.edu/web-team">the Web Team</a><br><br></p>
            </main>
            <div id="navigation" class="navigation">
